The paper discusses the use of repeated games to model interactions among wireless nodes in order to encourage cooperation and improve network performance. This topic falls under the intersection of game theory (cs.GT) and networking (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses various problems in wireless networks related to information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.MA) which are all relevant to the field of wireless networking.
